        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 7:42AM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 741 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles south of Columbia City, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Laud, Churubusco, Butler Center, Saint Johns, Blue Lake, Aboite,
Roanoke, Laotto, Raber, Arcola, Swan, Rolling Hills, Lake Everett,
Peabody, Columbia City, Leo-cedarville, Ege, Green Center, Dunfee,
and Lisbon.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 469 near mile marker 8, and between mile markers 29 and
30.
Interstate 69 in Indiana between mile markers 293 and 326.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
